We need to understand Aristotle's cosmology and what was wrong with it and what we learned

01:00:32.200 --> 01:00:35.680
about the universe that made us realize that that was limited.

01:00:35.680 --> 01:00:38.240
Like you just said, we need to understand Newton's laws.

01:00:38.240 --> 01:00:42.720
In fact, we can't teach science without teaching Newton's laws.

01:00:42.720 --> 01:00:47.200
And then we teach why they don't quite apply fully because of what we've learned since

01:00:47.200 --> 01:00:48.200
then.

01:00:48.200 --> 01:00:56.320
We teach science and to know science without knowing that history of ideas that are wrong.

01:00:56.320 --> 01:00:59.080
I mean in a certain sense limited.

