As I understand, art, which is not fully, there are also movements and things that, you know,

01:01:28.600 --> 01:01:33.400
ways that are things are done and you don't go out and do art the way it was done 20 years

01:01:33.400 --> 01:01:34.400
ago.

01:01:34.400 --> 01:01:35.880
So there is that sort of revision too.

01:01:35.880 --> 01:01:38.320
It's not quite the same sort of linearity.

01:01:38.320 --> 01:01:43.240
But maybe there's a little more commonality there than was represented.

01:01:43.240 --> 01:01:48.040
The other quick point I wanted to make was about this notion of not having everything

01:01:48.040 --> 01:01:49.520
just done by geniuses.

01:01:49.520 --> 01:01:51.760
I thought it was a very interesting part of the conversation.

01:01:51.760 --> 01:01:54.840
And there is this question of who owns art and who owns science?

01:01:54.840 --> 01:01:56.120
Who's it for?

01:01:56.120 --> 01:02:02.240
Is art just for professional artists in art departments or is it for everybody?

